about.description: Compute the Euclidean Distance Transform of a 1d, 2d, or 3d labeled image containing multiple labels in a single pass with support for anisotropic dimensions.
about.summary: Euclidean distance transform for multi-label 3D anisotropic images.

name: edt
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "edt" %}
{% set version = "2.0.1" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 335db434e06125ea2950c29a67a306ac73a8f906ef4b0c8ca269580ada2f833c

build:
  number: 0
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}
  host:
    - pbr
    - pip
    - python
    - numpy >=1.16.0
  run:
    - python
    - {{ pin_compatible('numpy') }}

test:
  imports:
    - edt

about:
  home: https://github.com/seung-lab/euclidean-distance-transform-3d
  license: GPL-3.0-or-later
  license_family: GPL
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: 'Euclidean distance transform for multi-label 3D anisotropic images.'
  description: Compute the Euclidean Distance Transform of a 1d, 2d, or 3d labeled 
      image containing multiple labels in a single pass with support for anisotropic 
      dimensions.

  doc_url: https://github.com/seung-lab/euclidean-distance-transform-3d
  dev_url: https://github.com/seung-lab/euclidean-distance-transform-3d

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - william-silversmith
smithy_version:
No azure token. Create a token and
put it in ~/.conda-smithy/azure.token
3.7.0
